webpackJsonp([0xd7733235aea0],{535:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{wordpressWpLessons:{id:"f364ebea-1e43-5704-8c23-2e116c4d6095",wordpress_id:6398,title:"Introducing Thimble",slug:"introducing-thimble",content:'<h2>Objectives and Overview</h2>\n<p><a href="https://thimble.mozilla.org/en-US/">Thimble</a> is a beginner friendly, web-based code editor created by the <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/foundation/">Mozilla Foundation</a>. Thimble is meant to help new learners build HTML, CSS, and JavaScript tools while having a place online to host and show projects.</p>\n<h3>Lesson Objectives:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a Thimble account</li>\n<li>Explore the Thimble interface</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h2 class="learn-activity">Activity: Create An Account</h2>\n<p>The first step is to navigate to <a href="https://thimble.mozilla.org/en-US/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://thimble.mozilla.org/en-US/</a> and click the <strong>Sign in or Create an account</strong> link in the top right corner of the interface:</p>\n<h2><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6425" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-1024x557.jpg" alt="thimble main page sign up for an account highlighted" width="625" height="340" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-1024x557.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-300x163.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-768x418.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-184x100.jpg 184w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-624x340.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-100x54.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-1-750x408.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></h2>\n<p>This will open up a new page that prompts you to select a <strong>username</strong>, enter an <strong>email address</strong>, and choose a <strong>password</strong>. Use the following criteria when creating these:</p>\n<p><strong>Username</strong>: This should be something identifiable, such as your first and last name, or your first initial and last name.</p>\n<p><strong>Email</strong>: You should use your DHF youth email address.</p>\n<p><strong>Password</strong>: Select one that is both secure and memorable. If you forget it, you&#8217;ll need to reset it via the Thimble interface.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve filled out those fields, click the <strong>Sign Up</strong> button:</p>\n<h2><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6424" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-1024x524.jpg" alt="entering fields to create a thimble account" width="625" height="320" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-1024x524.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-300x153.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-768x393.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-195x100.jpg 195w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-624x319.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-100x51.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-signup-2-750x384.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></h2>\n<p>From this point forward you can login with your username and password!</p>\n<h2>Navigating the Interface</h2>\n<p>Thimble has a clear, user-friendly interface, but let&#8217;s take a look at some of the basics. Once you&#8217;re logged in you&#8217;ll see your username in the top right corner. If you don&#8217;t see this, make sure that you&#8217;re logged in before proceeding. Otherwise, your work won&#8217;t save to your account!</p>\n<p>When you&#8217;re starting a new project you can click the &#8220;Start a project from scratch&#8221; button, but for now click on the &#8220;Get Started&#8221; link in the top left corner:</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-6430" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-1024x547.jpg" alt="" width="625" height="334" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-1024x547.jpg 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-300x160.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-768x410.jpg 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-187x100.jpg 187w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-624x333.jpg 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-100x53.jpg 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/mf-thimble-get-started-2-750x401.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></p>\n<p>Thimble supports Remixing as a tool for learning. You&#8217;re able to remix template projects to test your skills, and you can also share your project for others to remix!</p>\n<p>For right now, take some time to explore the Thimble interface before moving on.</p>\n'}},pathContext:{}}}});
